questions.question:
Let A[1, ..., n] be an array storing a bit (0 or 1) at each location, and f(m) is a function whose time complexity is Theta(m). Consider the following program fragment written in a C like language:

counter = 0;
for (i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    if (A[i] == 1) counter++;
    else { f(counter); counter = 0; }
}

The complexity of this program fragment is:

A. Theta(n^2)
B. Theta(n log n) and O(n^2)
C. Theta(n)
D. O(n)

Consider the following segment of C-code:

int j, n;
j = 1;
while (j <= n)
    j = j * 2;

The number of comparisons made in the execution of the loop for any n >= 1 is:

A. floor(log_2(n)) + 1
B. ceil(log_2(n))
C. floor(log_2(n))
D. ceil(log_2(n)) + 1

What is the time complexity of the following recursive function?

int DoSomething (int n) {
    if (n <= 2)
        return 1;
    else
        return (DoSomething (floor(sqrt(n))) + n);
}

A. Theta(n^2)
B. Theta(n log_2 n)
C. Theta(log_2 n)
D. Theta(log_2(log_2 n))
